WEBVTT

00:02.836 --> 00:05.238
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

00:20.687 --> 00:22.756
Katheryn:
SPOKE TO GOVERNOR HARVEY.

00:22.756 --> 00:24.457
HE AND HIS WIFE
SEND BIRTHDAY WISHES.

00:24.457 --> 00:25.792
WHAT'S THAT GONNA
COST US?

00:25.792 --> 00:27.794
A FUNDRAISER DINNER
NEXT MONTH.

00:27.794 --> 00:29.462
I'M NOT SURE
I WANT TO DO THAT.

00:29.462 --> 00:32.265
I THOUGHT
YOU'D SAY THAT.

00:32.265 --> 00:33.399
ARE YOU THINKING
ABOUT RUNNING?

00:33.399 --> 00:34.467
I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

00:34.467 --> 00:36.336
But you said that
for a reason.

00:38.338 --> 00:40.373
AND SILENCE.

00:40.373 --> 00:41.908
Okay.

00:43.476 --> 00:45.145
WHAT TIME WILL YOU
BE HOME?

00:45.145 --> 00:46.547
I HAVE NO IDEA.
THIS CASE HAS GOT

00:46.547 --> 00:48.281
MORE TWISTS AND TURNS
THAN A ROLLER COASTER.

00:48.281 --> 00:49.816
YOU'RE THE JUDGE.
[ SCOFFS ]

00:49.816 --> 00:51.985
TELL THEM TO WRAP IT UP
SO YOU CAN GET HOME.

00:51.985 --> 00:54.087
YEAH, I'LL DO MY BEST.

00:54.087 --> 00:56.990
JIM,
IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY.

00:56.990 --> 00:59.359
And our children will be
home tonight

00:59.359 --> 01:00.734
for a surprise dinner.

01:00.734 --> 01:02.235
WHY ARE THEY DOING THAT?

01:02.235 --> 01:03.369
YOU'RE 50.

01:03.369 --> 01:04.971
IT'S A BIG DEAL.

01:04.971 --> 01:06.139
Okay.

01:06.139 --> 01:07.908
I'LL TRY TO GET HOME
BY 9:00.

01:07.908 --> 01:09.809
6:00,
AND NOT A MOMENT LATER.

01:09.809 --> 01:12.178
FINE. FINE.

01:12.178 --> 01:13.413
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

01:13.413 --> 01:15.248
HEY,
I THINK THAT'S, UH,

01:15.248 --> 01:17.083
I THINK THAT'S DAVID
AT THE DOOR. I GOT TO GO.

01:17.083 --> 01:18.251
OKAY.

01:18.251 --> 01:19.319
TELL HIM I SAID HI.

01:19.319 --> 01:20.654
WILL DO.

01:20.654 --> 01:22.255
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

01:39.806 --> 01:40.941
HI.

01:40.941 --> 01:42.142
HI.

01:42.142 --> 01:45.712
ARE YOU...CANDY?

01:45.712 --> 01:49.082
YEAH.

01:49.082 --> 01:50.551
ARE YOU JIM?

01:52.085 --> 01:53.386
YES.

01:53.386 --> 01:55.388
HMM.

01:55.388 --> 01:57.591
COME ON IN.

02:01.434 --> 02:06.406
I THOUGHT I WAS COMING TO SEE
SOME OLD MAN.

02:06.406 --> 02:09.209
I AM OLD.

02:09.209 --> 02:11.812
YOU DON'T LOOK IT.

02:11.812 --> 02:14.981
FLATTERY WILL
GET YOU EVERYWHERE.

02:14.981 --> 02:19.919
WELL, MONEY...

02:19.919 --> 02:21.154
WILL GET YOU...

02:24.124 --> 02:26.727
...THIS.

02:26.727 --> 02:29.996
THEN IT'S A GOOD THING
I HAVE SOME.

02:29.996 --> 02:32.332
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:37.170 --> 02:40.173
‐‐Captions by VITAC‐‐
www.vitac.com

02:40.173 --> 02:43.176
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

02:47.380 --> 02:50.150
SO, YOU WORKED
FOR THE WELDRICKS?

02:50.150 --> 02:52.118
MM‐HMM.
FOR 20 YEARS.

02:52.118 --> 02:53.854
AND MY MOTHER BEFORE ME.

02:53.854 --> 02:55.321
SAD.

02:55.321 --> 02:56.422
CANCER, RIGHT?

02:56.422 --> 02:58.892
I'M NOT AT LIBERTY
TO SAY.

02:58.892 --> 03:00.160
WELL, DARLING,
IF YOU'RE TRYING TO BECOME

03:00.160 --> 03:02.068
GAINFULLY EMPLOYED,
YOU SHOULD BE MORE FORTHCOMING.

03:02.068 --> 03:04.771
ANYTHING YOU NEED TO KNOW
ABOUT ME ‐‐ ANYTHING AT ALL ‐‐

03:04.771 --> 03:06.272
I'M WILLING TO SHARE.

03:06.272 --> 03:08.542
BUT I CAN'T TALK ABOUT
MY PREVIOUS EMPLOYERS.

03:08.542 --> 03:11.411
SO, WHAT WOULD SHE SAY
ABOUT YOU,

03:11.411 --> 03:13.880
IF SHE WERE ALIVE,
THAT IS?

03:13.880 --> 03:16.449
WELL, SINCE SHE CAN'T,
I CAN TELL YOU

03:16.449 --> 03:20.053
THAT I WAS HER HOUSEKEEPER
AND CAREGIVER FOR MANY YEARS.

03:20.053 --> 03:21.822
SHE WAS
A WONDERFUL WOMAN.

03:21.822 --> 03:24.991
THAT HUSBAND OF HERS ‐‐
SUCH A WANDERING EYE,

03:24.991 --> 03:26.893
AND I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT
FOR FEMALES.

03:28.061 --> 03:29.429
IT'S A SMALL TOWN.

03:29.429 --> 03:31.998
WAS HE REALLY SLEEPING
WITH THAT YOUNG MAN?

03:33.466 --> 03:38.905
MRS. CRYER,
I'M WASTING YOUR TIME.

03:38.905 --> 03:41.307
I DON'T THINK
THIS IS THE PLACE FOR ME.

03:41.307 --> 03:43.343
BUT I'M SURE
YOU'LL FIND SOMEONE

03:43.343 --> 03:46.547
WHO'LL BE
GREAT FOR THIS JOB.

03:46.547 --> 03:48.682
SIT DOWN, HANNA.

03:58.324 --> 04:00.026
MY FAMILY HAS BEEN
KNOWN

04:00.026 --> 04:02.035
TO HAVE A FEW SKELETONS
IN OUR CLOSET,

04:02.035 --> 04:04.437
AND IT'S VERY IMPORTANT TO ME
THAT THEY STAY THERE,

04:04.437 --> 04:08.274
ESPECIALLY IN THIS DAY
OF SOCIAL MEDIA.

04:08.274 --> 04:11.144
SO EVERYONE I HIRE COMES
UNDER EXTREME SCRUTINY.

04:11.144 --> 04:12.478
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

04:12.478 --> 04:14.515
YES.

04:14.515 --> 04:17.150
GOOD.

04:17.150 --> 04:19.119
SO, DOES THAT MEAN
I'M HIRED?

04:19.119 --> 04:21.622
YES,
AND YOU CAN START RIGHT NOW.

04:21.622 --> 04:22.723
CELINE?

04:22.723 --> 04:23.890
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

04:23.890 --> 04:25.458
WILL YOU SHOW HANNA
WHAT SHE'LL BE DOING?

04:25.458 --> 04:28.529
YES, MA'AM.

04:28.529 --> 04:30.631
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

04:30.631 --> 04:31.898
DON'T THANK ME
YET.

04:31.898 --> 04:34.200
YOU HAVEN'T MET
MY FAMILY.

04:34.200 --> 04:39.472
AND, HANNA, CONFIDENTIALITY IS
KEY TO KEEPING YOUR JOB.

04:46.112 --> 04:49.683
I AM SO HAPPY THAT YOU'RE
GONNA BE WORKING WITH ME.

04:49.683 --> 04:50.851
THANK YOU.

04:50.851 --> 04:52.753
GOSH. OH, YOU'RE WELCOME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:52.753 --> 04:56.022
THANK YOU SO MUCH FOR GETTING ME
THIS INTERVIEW, CELINE.

04:56.022 --> 04:57.658
WHAT ARE FRIENDS FOR,
HANNA?

04:57.658 --> 04:59.325
I'D DO ANYTHING FOR YOU.
MM.

04:59.325 --> 05:02.402
HOW'S YOUR FAMILY?

05:02.402 --> 05:04.004
OH, GOSH. MY FAMILY.

05:04.004 --> 05:05.405
MY KIDS ARE GOOD.

05:05.405 --> 05:06.573
CAN'T COMPLAIN.

05:06.573 --> 05:08.809
THEY'RE OUT OF TROUBLE,
WHICH IS ALWAYS WONDERFUL.

05:08.809 --> 05:10.076
HOW ABOUT YOUR HUSBAND?

05:10.076 --> 05:12.412
YEAH, YOU NOTICED
I DIDN'T MENTION HIM, HUH?

05:12.412 --> 05:14.214
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

05:14.214 --> 05:15.481
I DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

05:15.481 --> 05:16.950
ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

05:16.950 --> 05:18.084
HOW'S BENNY?

05:18.084 --> 05:19.452
OH, HE'S GREAT.

05:19.452 --> 05:20.787
GIRL, HE'S TRYING
TO GET A TOW TRUCK.

05:20.787 --> 05:21.788
IS HE REALLY?

05:21.788 --> 05:22.923
START HIS OWN BUSINESS.

05:22.923 --> 05:24.825
OH, BLESS HIM.
YES.

05:24.825 --> 05:26.092
LOVE THAT KID.

05:26.092 --> 05:27.360
HOW'S HIS DAD?

05:27.360 --> 05:29.730
MM,
AND WE WON'T TALK ABOUT <i>HIM.</i>

05:29.730 --> 05:30.831
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

05:30.831 --> 05:32.265
THAT BAD, HUH?

05:32.265 --> 05:34.635
YES. PLEASE.
[ SIGHS ]

05:34.635 --> 05:36.036
AND I CAN'T BELIEVE
I'M GONNA SAY THIS,

05:36.036 --> 05:37.237
BUT I'M SO GLAD
THAT WOMAN DIED.

05:37.237 --> 05:39.105
THAT IS NOT NICE,
CELINE.

05:39.105 --> 05:41.775
WELL, SHE WAS KIND OF CRAZY,
HANNA.

05:41.775 --> 05:44.244
WELL,
WE WERE FRIENDS, THANK YOU.

05:44.244 --> 05:46.279
OKAY. SORRY.

05:46.279 --> 05:47.514
WHAT'S SHE LIKE?

05:47.514 --> 05:49.415
KATHERYN?
MM‐HMM.

05:49.415 --> 05:51.852
KATHERYN ‐‐
SHE'S, UM...

05:51.852 --> 05:52.986
SHE'S A HANDFUL.

05:52.986 --> 05:54.921
[ Laughing ]
YEAH, I CAN TELL.

05:54.921 --> 05:56.256
BUT IF YOU DO YOUR JOB,

05:56.256 --> 05:58.324
YOU KNOW,
YOU WON'T HAVE A PROBLEM.

05:58.324 --> 05:59.793
OKAY.

05:59.793 --> 06:00.901
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:00.901 --> 06:02.503
WHAT?
SOMETHING'S NOT RIGHT?

06:02.503 --> 06:03.537
I DON'T KNOW.

06:03.537 --> 06:05.739
YOU KNOW,
YOU JUST THINK YOU HAVE

06:05.739 --> 06:08.374
YOUR LIFE SETTLED IN
AT ONE POINT, AND ‐‐

06:08.374 --> 06:10.611
AND IT ALL GETS
TURNED AROUND.

06:10.611 --> 06:13.446
BUT, BLESS THE LORD,
I HAVE A JOB.

06:13.446 --> 06:14.548
YES, YOU DO.

06:14.548 --> 06:16.149
SO, WHAT DO I DO?

06:16.149 --> 06:18.585
FIRST THING WE'RE GONNA DO IS
GET YOU FITTED FOR A UNIFORM.

06:18.585 --> 06:20.521
I THINK SOMETHING WILL FIT YOU.
I'M NOT SURE.

06:20.521 --> 06:21.688
OH, YOU WATCH IT.
WATCH YOUR MOUTH.

06:21.688 --> 06:23.957
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

06:23.957 --> 06:25.258
OH.

06:27.160 --> 06:28.228
[ SIGHS ]

06:28.228 --> 06:29.530
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:29.530 --> 06:30.697
[ LAUGHS ]

06:30.697 --> 06:31.865
WOW.

06:31.865 --> 06:33.800
[ LAUGHS ]

06:33.800 --> 06:36.637
I SHOULD BE SAYING "WOW."

06:36.637 --> 06:38.138
[ SIGHS ]

06:38.138 --> 06:40.173
YOU REALLY ARE HANDSOME.

06:40.173 --> 06:44.210
OH, AND YOU REALLY, REALLY,
REALLY ARE BEAUTIFUL.

06:44.210 --> 06:47.147
YOU'RE TOO HANDSOME
TO HAVE TO PAY FOR SEX.

06:47.147 --> 06:49.282
AND YOU'RE TOO BEAUTIFUL
TO BE SELLING IT.

06:49.282 --> 06:50.450
[ LAUGHS ]
HMM.

06:50.450 --> 06:52.352
I GUESS
EVERYBODY HAS A STORY.

06:52.352 --> 06:53.520
I GUESS.

06:53.520 --> 06:55.556
SO, WHAT IS YOUR STORY,
CANDY?

06:55.556 --> 06:58.324
MINE IS
TO NOT KISS AND TELL.

06:58.324 --> 06:59.926
OH. Shh.

06:59.926 --> 07:01.735
MM‐HMM.
[ LAUGHS ]

07:01.735 --> 07:02.869
YOU?

07:02.869 --> 07:04.337
WELL, I THINK WE SHOULD

07:04.337 --> 07:07.140
GET TO KNOW EACH OTHER
A LITTLE BETTER FIRST.

07:07.140 --> 07:10.511
DOES THAT MEAN, UH,
YOU WANT TO SEE ME AGAIN?

07:10.511 --> 07:15.849
I WOULD LOVE [LAUGHS] ‐‐
I WOULD LOVE TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

07:15.849 --> 07:18.418
REALLY?
REALLY.

07:18.418 --> 07:19.653
MM.

07:19.653 --> 07:21.888
[ SIGHS ]
WELL, YOU'LL BE THE FIRST.

07:21.888 --> 07:24.124
NO. COME ON. THAT'S INSANE.
[ LAUGHS ]

07:24.124 --> 07:26.893
REALLY?
YEP, REALLY.

07:26.893 --> 07:27.894
[ LAUGHS ]

07:27.894 --> 07:29.696
WELL, I'M HONORED.

07:29.696 --> 07:32.165
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:36.469 --> 07:39.640
HERE IS...

07:39.640 --> 07:42.676
MY PERSONAL NUMBER.

07:42.676 --> 07:46.446
WOW.
UH‐HUH.

07:46.446 --> 07:50.751
I WANT YOU TO USE IT...
ANYTIME.

07:50.751 --> 07:55.121
AND I MIGHT'VE ACCIDENTALLY LEFT
SOME MONEY ON THE DRESSER.

07:55.121 --> 07:58.424
MONEY ON THE DRESSER.

07:58.424 --> 08:01.234
YOU MUST BE
IN THE LEGAL PROFESSION.

08:01.234 --> 08:03.269
NO MONEY EXCHANGES HANDS.

08:03.269 --> 08:04.705
Shh, shh, shh.

08:04.705 --> 08:06.507
MINE'S
NOT TO KISS AND TELL.

08:06.507 --> 08:07.874
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:10.911 --> 08:12.045
HANNA.

08:12.045 --> 08:13.647
YES, MA'AM?

08:13.647 --> 08:16.550
BE SURE
TO CLEAN BEHIND THESE DRAPES.

08:16.550 --> 08:19.085
THEY COLLECT DUST
LIKE A GRAVE.

08:19.085 --> 08:20.153
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:20.153 --> 08:22.222
THE LAST MAID
NEVER DID.

08:22.222 --> 08:24.324
YES, MA'AM.

08:24.324 --> 08:26.693
AND MAKE SURE CELINE HAS
BOTH MY CHILDREN'S ROOMS READY.

08:26.693 --> 08:28.829
YES, MA'AM.

08:28.829 --> 08:31.097
AND WYATT HAS ALLERGIES.

08:31.097 --> 08:33.634
ALLERGIC
TO EVERYTHING.

08:36.236 --> 08:38.839
MAKE SURE THERE ARE NO
FABRIC SOFTENER ON HIS SHEETS.

08:38.839 --> 08:40.473
YES, MA'AM.

08:40.473 --> 08:43.409
WATER ALL THESE PLANTS.

08:43.409 --> 08:45.245
DO YOU HAVE CHILDREN?

08:45.245 --> 08:47.180
YES, MA'AM, I DO.
HOW MANY?

08:47.180 --> 08:49.683
TWO.
A BOY AND A GIRL.

08:49.683 --> 08:51.484
SAME FOR ME.

08:51.484 --> 08:53.319
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:53.319 --> 08:55.956
KAT?

08:56.857 --> 08:58.424
IN HERE.

08:58.424 --> 09:00.093
[ SIGHS ]

09:00.093 --> 09:02.368
THERE YOU ARE.

09:02.368 --> 09:04.638
OOH. [ SIGHS ]

09:04.638 --> 09:07.040
WE DID IT.

09:07.040 --> 09:08.208
WHAT?

09:08.208 --> 09:09.610
THE MERGER.

09:09.610 --> 09:12.546
CONGRATULATIONS.

09:12.546 --> 09:14.380
OH, THANK YOU

09:14.380 --> 09:16.316
FOR ALL THE PHONE CALLS
TO THE BOARD.

09:16.316 --> 09:18.619
MM, DON'T MENTION IT.

09:18.619 --> 09:21.555
THANK YOU FOR TAKING WYATT
INTO YOUR FACILITY.

09:21.555 --> 09:24.024
THAT YOU DON'T HAVE
TO MENTION.

09:24.024 --> 09:25.291
I HAVE BEEN WAITING

09:25.291 --> 09:27.961
FOR THE WILSONS TO SELL
THEIR FACILITIES FOR YEARS.

09:27.961 --> 09:30.396
MY BIGGEST COMPETITOR IS
OUT OF BUSINESS.

09:30.396 --> 09:31.397
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:31.397 --> 09:32.699
THIS IS FANTASTIC.

09:32.699 --> 09:34.701
WE NEED CHAMPAGNE.

09:34.701 --> 09:36.169
YOU CAN'T HAVE CHAMPAGNE.

09:36.169 --> 09:37.571
NO, BUT YOU CAN.

09:37.571 --> 09:39.139
I'LL HAVE SPARKLING WATER.

09:39.139 --> 09:40.206
WE SHOULD TOAST.

09:40.206 --> 09:41.474
ABSOLUTELY.

09:41.474 --> 09:42.976
CHAMPAGNE, PLEASE,
HANNA,

09:42.976 --> 09:45.779
AND SOME SPARKLING WATER
FOR VERONICA.

09:56.557 --> 09:59.192
WHO IS THAT?

09:59.192 --> 10:00.594
WHO?

10:00.594 --> 10:02.769
THAT HEIFER
WHO THREW ME HER COAT.

10:02.769 --> 10:06.840
OH, YOU HAD THE HONOR
OF MEETING MISS VERONICA.

10:06.840 --> 10:08.008
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHERE THIS GOES.

10:08.008 --> 10:09.342
HERE. I'LL TAKE IT.

10:09.342 --> 10:11.578
SHE IS THE WORST.

10:11.578 --> 10:13.246
UGH.

10:20.286 --> 10:22.856
I CAN'T STAND
BLACK PEOPLE LIKE THAT.

10:22.856 --> 10:24.324
LIKE WHAT?

10:24.324 --> 10:25.926
WHO THINK THEY'RE BETTER
THAN EVERYBODY ELSE.

10:25.926 --> 10:27.327
SHE PROBABLY AIN'T GOT
A POT TO PISS IN

10:27.327 --> 10:28.529
NOR A WINDOW
TO THROW IT OUT OF.

10:28.529 --> 10:29.763
OH, NO, NO.

10:29.763 --> 10:31.497
SHE'S GOT MONEY.
MM.

10:31.497 --> 10:33.199
SHE'S WORTH $20 MILLION.

10:33.199 --> 10:34.434
WHAT?
MM‐HMM.

10:34.434 --> 10:35.869
SHE MARRIED INTO IT?

10:35.869 --> 10:37.437
NO.
HER HUSBAND'S A JUDGE.

10:37.437 --> 10:39.506
HE WORKS WITH JIM,
KATHERYN'S HUSBAND.

10:39.506 --> 10:40.574
HE WHITE?

10:40.574 --> 10:43.276
NO. BLACK.

10:43.276 --> 10:45.679
AND SHE WANTS
SPARKLING WATER.

10:45.679 --> 10:46.713
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:46.713 --> 10:48.281
SHE'S ACTUALLY
A RECOVERING ALCOHOLIC.

10:48.281 --> 10:49.282
MM.

10:49.282 --> 10:51.451
BEEN SOBER 20 YEARS,
I HEAR.

10:51.451 --> 10:53.386
SHE FOUNDED THIS, UM,

10:53.386 --> 10:57.958
SUPERDUPER PROMINENT
REHAB CENTER DOWN BY THE BEACH.

10:57.958 --> 10:59.626
[ SCOFFS ] GREAT.

10:59.626 --> 11:01.568
THE BLACK BETTY FORD.

11:01.568 --> 11:02.836
[ LAUGHS ]

11:02.836 --> 11:04.571
[ Singsong voice ]
YOU'RE GONNA GET INTO TROUBLE

11:04.571 --> 11:05.739
IF YOU KEEP TALKING
LIKE THAT.

11:05.739 --> 11:07.073
[ LAUGHS ]

11:07.073 --> 11:08.742
THAT'S HOW YOU'RE GONNA
START THE DAY, HUH?

11:08.742 --> 11:10.476
YES, I AM.
YOU WANT SOME?

11:10.476 --> 11:11.812
[ Laughing ] NO.

11:17.851 --> 11:19.052
YOU AND DAVID WILL BE
HERE TONIGHT

11:19.052 --> 11:20.120
FOR JIM'S BIRTHDAY PARTY?

11:20.120 --> 11:21.588
OF COURSE WE WILL.

11:21.588 --> 11:24.024
HOW OFTEN DOES
OUR GOOD FRIEND TURN 50?

11:24.024 --> 11:25.191
MM.

11:25.191 --> 11:27.427
HOW'S HE FEELING
ABOUT TURNING 50, ANYWAY?

11:27.427 --> 11:28.428
I'M STILL WAITING

11:28.428 --> 11:30.263
FOR THE MIDLIFE CRISIS
TO KICK IN.

11:30.263 --> 11:32.132
I EXPECT A RED SPORTS CAR

11:32.132 --> 11:35.035
TO SHOW UP IN THE DRIVEWAY
ANY SECOND.

11:35.035 --> 11:37.971
HE'LL PROBABLY TRADE ME IN
FOR A YOUNGER VERSION.

11:37.971 --> 11:39.773
NOT IF HE KNOWS
WHAT'S GOOD FOR HIM.

11:39.773 --> 11:41.107
MM.

11:41.107 --> 11:42.809
THAT'S ONE OF THE PERKS
OF BEING AN HEIRESS.

11:42.809 --> 11:44.545
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:44.545 --> 11:45.779
WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT.

11:45.779 --> 11:46.813
THIS IS SOME THERAPY.

11:46.813 --> 11:48.014
WHY ARE YOU STILL ARGUING
ABOUT THIS?

11:48.014 --> 11:49.049
WHY DO I WANT MORE HEROIN
WHEN I'M WITH YOU

11:49.049 --> 11:50.116
THAN WITHOUT YOU?

11:50.116 --> 11:51.552
FOLLOW ME
EVERY‐DAMN‐WHERE I GO.

11:51.552 --> 11:52.886
YES I DO,
AND I JUST TOLD YOU.

11:52.886 --> 11:54.220
Veronica: OH, WYATT.

11:54.220 --> 11:55.355
HOW ARE YOU?

11:55.355 --> 11:57.357
BETTER IF I DIDN'T
HAVE TO HAVE THIS GUY

11:57.357 --> 11:58.525
FOLLOWING ME EVERYWHERE.

11:58.525 --> 11:59.626
IT'S ALL RIGHT, WYATT.

11:59.626 --> 12:01.334
HI, SON.
HI, MOM.

12:01.334 --> 12:02.402
HOW ARE YOU?

12:02.402 --> 12:03.737
GOOD.

12:03.737 --> 12:06.172
HELLO, JEFFREY.

12:06.172 --> 12:07.541
HI.

12:07.541 --> 12:09.976
SON.

12:09.976 --> 12:11.912
MOM.

12:11.912 --> 12:13.914
HOW ARE YOU?

12:13.914 --> 12:16.249
[ SCOFFS ]

12:16.249 --> 12:18.251
GREAT.

12:18.251 --> 12:20.554
COULDN'T BE BETTER.

12:20.554 --> 12:21.922
WHOA.
WHERE YOU GOING?

12:21.922 --> 12:23.189
TO THE BATHROOM.

12:23.189 --> 12:24.691
CAN I DO THAT ALONE?

12:24.691 --> 12:27.393
WYATT, YOU KNOW JEFFREY HAS
TO GO WITH YOU

12:27.393 --> 12:28.829
FOR THE FIRST 60 DAYS.

12:28.829 --> 12:30.263
IT'S THE <i>BATHROOM.</i>

12:35.836 --> 12:38.438
WYATT,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

12:39.439 --> 12:41.307
STOP IT!

12:42.342 --> 12:43.343
SEE?

12:43.343 --> 12:44.611
GOT NOTHING.

12:44.611 --> 12:46.346
MY SON.

12:46.346 --> 12:47.748
THAT'S ‐‐
SORRY ABOUT THAT.

12:47.748 --> 12:49.750
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

12:49.750 --> 12:52.185
WE HAVE OUR HANDS FULL
WITH THAT ONE, I TELL YOU.

12:52.185 --> 12:53.754
BUT HE WILL BE FINE.

12:53.754 --> 12:56.022
I WILL SEE YOU TONIGHT
AT DINNER.

12:56.022 --> 12:57.390
OKAY.

12:57.390 --> 12:58.525
7:00.

12:58.525 --> 13:00.460
[ SMOOCHES ] 7:00.

13:00.460 --> 13:03.003
HAT, COAT, PLEASE!

13:04.871 --> 13:07.107
HEY.
HI.

13:07.107 --> 13:10.410
OH, PLEASE TELL ME YOU DIDN'T
CROSS THE LIVING ROOM.

13:10.410 --> 13:11.612
I DID.

13:11.612 --> 13:13.914
OH, GOD, DON'T.
ALWAYS USE THE BACK STAIRS.

13:13.914 --> 13:16.082
SHE DOESN'T LIKE TO SEE
EITHER ONE OF US

13:16.082 --> 13:17.784
UNLESS SHE CALLS FIRST,
OKAY?

13:17.784 --> 13:20.286
OKAY. I SEE. WHY?

13:20.286 --> 13:23.557
I DON'T KNOW.
THAT'S JUST THE WAY SHE IS.

13:23.557 --> 13:25.258
ALL RIGHT.

13:25.258 --> 13:26.927
WELL, THIS IS HER SON,
WYATT'S, ROOM.

13:26.927 --> 13:29.129
THIRD STINT IN REHAB,
BY THE WAY.

13:29.129 --> 13:30.496
MM.

13:30.496 --> 13:33.166
HE'S ALWAYS WITH THIS YOUNG MAN
NAMED JEFFREY, WHO ‐‐

13:33.166 --> 13:35.769
HE'S KIND OF LIKE HIS,
I DON'T KNOW,

13:35.769 --> 13:36.770
LIFE COACH, COUNSELOR.

13:36.770 --> 13:38.071
I'M NOT SURE
WHAT TO CALL HIM.

13:38.071 --> 13:41.007
HELP ME FINISH THE ROOM,
YEAH?

13:42.075 --> 13:44.444
HI, CELINE.

13:45.612 --> 13:46.780
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

13:46.780 --> 13:47.948
WHO'S THIS?

13:47.948 --> 13:49.550
WYATT,
I'M NOT TALKING TO YOU

13:49.550 --> 13:50.851
UNLESS YOU PUT CLOTHES ON.

13:50.851 --> 13:52.753
WE'RE ALL BORN
THIS WAY.

13:52.753 --> 13:54.921
JUST CAME TO USE
MY BATHROOM.

13:54.921 --> 13:57.524
OKAY.

13:59.425 --> 14:00.767
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

14:00.767 --> 14:02.536
HE WAS BORN DEPRIVED.

14:02.536 --> 14:03.804
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

14:03.804 --> 14:05.806
SORRY ABOUT THAT.
EXCUSE ME.

14:05.806 --> 14:07.574
MM‐HMM.

14:09.175 --> 14:10.944
HE GOT TO GO TO THE BATHROOM
WITH HIM, TOO?

14:10.944 --> 14:12.178
SEE? MM‐HMM.

14:12.178 --> 14:13.246
OOH, GIRL.

14:13.246 --> 14:14.615
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

14:20.887 --> 14:22.623
SO,
NOTHING'S CHANGED.

14:22.623 --> 14:24.725
ACTUALLY,
IT HAS, MS. CRYER.

14:24.725 --> 14:27.027
I MEAN,
HE'S BEEN CLEAN FOR 47 DAYS.

14:27.027 --> 14:28.695
BUT HE STILL GETS
VERY AGITATED

14:28.695 --> 14:30.664
AT HAVING TO DEAL
WITH THE REAL WORLD.

14:30.664 --> 14:32.165
I TOLD YOU,
YOU HAVE TO BE PATIENT.

14:32.165 --> 14:33.700
YOUR MOTHER KEEPS
REITERATING THAT.

14:33.700 --> 14:35.135
WILL YOU BE STAYING
ALL WEEKEND?

14:35.135 --> 14:37.070
WELL, THAT'S THE ONLY WAY
WE COULD LET HIM OUT.

14:37.070 --> 14:39.372
VERY WELL, THEN.

14:39.372 --> 14:41.174
I'LL HAVE THEM PREPARE
THE GUEST ROOM.

14:41.174 --> 14:44.310
OKAY, AND I'LL HAVE TO STAY
IN HIS ROOM.

14:44.310 --> 14:45.478
RIGHT.

14:45.478 --> 14:47.714
[ SIGHS ] HONEY.

14:47.714 --> 14:49.850
I SEE YOU MADE IT,
AND NOT A MOMENT TOO SOON.

14:49.850 --> 14:51.317
HI, JEFFREY.
WHY? WHAT'S UP?

14:51.317 --> 14:52.352
YOUR SON.

14:56.256 --> 14:57.390
WYATT,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

14:57.390 --> 14:58.825
DAD.

14:58.825 --> 15:01.067
PUT YOUR CLOTHES ON.
LISTEN.

15:01.067 --> 15:02.836
I SAID
PUT YOUR DAMN CLOTHES ON NOW!

15:02.836 --> 15:04.037
I'LL GET IT.
I GOT IT.

15:05.205 --> 15:06.607
WHAT IS THE MATTER
WITH YOU?

15:06.607 --> 15:07.674
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

15:07.674 --> 15:09.810
YOU CAN'T
WANDER AROUND THE HOUSE NAKED.

15:10.677 --> 15:11.745
UM...

15:11.745 --> 15:13.313
JEFFREY, AM I GONNA

15:13.313 --> 15:14.848
HAVE TO TALK TO YOUR FATHER
ABOUT THIS, HMM?

15:14.848 --> 15:15.916
NO, HE ‐‐

15:15.916 --> 15:17.317
WHAT ARE YOU DOING OVER THERE?
ANYTHING?

15:17.317 --> 15:18.484
I'M SPENDING A LOT OF MONEY
SO THAT YOU CAN HELP MY SON.

15:18.484 --> 15:20.086
ARE YOU HELPING MY SON?

15:20.086 --> 15:21.354
YES, MR. CRYER.
ANY SUCCESS?

15:21.354 --> 15:22.723
HE'S DOING A LOT BETTER.
REALLY?

15:22.723 --> 15:24.758
BUT I'M ONLY AS GOOD
AS MY PATIENT ALLOWS ME TO BE.

15:24.758 --> 15:25.926
WYATT,
YOU AND I HAD A DEAL.

15:25.926 --> 15:27.794
I'M TRYING.
WELL, TRY HARDER!

15:27.794 --> 15:30.564
I NEED A DRINK.
WYATT.

15:30.564 --> 15:31.865
YOU KNOW
YOU CAN'T DRINK.

15:31.865 --> 15:33.233
I KNOW, BUT THAT DOESN'T STOP ME
FROM WANTING A DRINK.

15:33.233 --> 15:34.935
DO YOU NOT EVEN KNOW
THE POINT OF REHAB?

15:34.935 --> 15:36.136
JIM,
DON'T GET WORKED UP.

15:36.136 --> 15:37.137
WHAT?

15:37.137 --> 15:38.271
IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY,

15:38.271 --> 15:39.940
AND WE HAVE
A LOVELY EVENING PLANNED.

15:39.940 --> 15:42.609
DON'T ‐‐
WYATT, COOL IT.

15:42.609 --> 15:44.611
JIM, ENOUGH.

15:44.611 --> 15:45.979
NO, I ‐‐
WE HAVE BEEN THROUGH THIS.

15:45.979 --> 15:47.380
WE HAVE ALREADY TALKED,
AND ‐‐

15:47.380 --> 15:49.716
MOM. DAD.
Shh. Shh.

15:49.716 --> 15:51.785
HEY, SWEETHEART.
HOW ARE YOU? MWAH!

15:51.785 --> 15:53.587
GOOD. HOW ARE YOU?
JUST FINE.

15:53.587 --> 15:55.656
JEFFREY.
HEY, KIDDO.

15:55.656 --> 15:57.257
ARE YOU TAKING CARE
OF MY BROTHER?

15:57.257 --> 15:58.491
AS BEST
AS HE'LL LET ME.

15:58.491 --> 16:01.101
I'LL TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.
COME ON!

16:01.101 --> 16:02.235
OBVIOUSLY,
YOU'RE HAVING ISSUES WITH IT.

16:02.235 --> 16:03.269
WHERE ARE YOU?

16:03.269 --> 16:04.538
JIM, JEFFREY IS
STAYING ALL WEEKEND.

16:04.538 --> 16:05.606
HE'S STAYING
IN HIS ROOM.

16:05.606 --> 16:06.573
HE IS WATCHING
EVERY MINUTE.

16:06.573 --> 16:07.440
EVERYBODY...

16:07.440 --> 16:08.441
AND THAT'S ALL WE CAN
HOPE FOR.

16:08.441 --> 16:09.643
...THIS IS
A GOOD FRIEND OF MINE.

16:09.643 --> 16:10.744
THIS IS CANDACE.

16:10.744 --> 16:12.278
HI.
Wyatt: HI.

16:12.278 --> 16:13.514
HI.

16:13.514 --> 16:15.148
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:15.148 --> 16:17.584
NICE TO MEET YOU ALL.

16:17.584 --> 16:18.885
Katheryn: YOU TOO.

16:24.424 --> 16:27.528
SO, THIS IS MY ROOM.

16:27.528 --> 16:29.229
WOW.

16:29.229 --> 16:31.131
WHAT?

16:31.131 --> 16:32.733
YOUR HOUSE IS
BEAUTIFUL.

16:32.733 --> 16:34.000
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:34.000 --> 16:37.504
IT'S MY PARENTS' HOUSE,
AND THEY NEVER LET ME FORGET IT.

16:37.504 --> 16:40.741
WELL, IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

16:40.741 --> 16:41.975
COME ON,

16:41.975 --> 16:44.144
I'M SURE YOUR PARENTS' HOUSE IS
JUST AS BEAUTIFUL.

16:44.144 --> 16:45.712
NO, NOT REALLY.

16:45.712 --> 16:48.915
YOU'RE JOKING.
NO. I'M NOT.

16:48.915 --> 16:51.184
WELL,
MY HOUSE IS YOUR HOUSE.

16:51.184 --> 16:52.519
THANK YOU.

16:52.519 --> 16:55.488
OH. HERE.

16:55.488 --> 16:58.725
TAKE A LOOK AT THIS.

16:58.725 --> 17:00.360
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:00.360 --> 17:01.367
YOU RODE HORSES?

17:01.367 --> 17:03.604
YEAH.
THAT WAS BUSTER.

17:03.604 --> 17:05.438
HE DIED A YEAR AGO.

17:05.438 --> 17:06.607
I'M SORRY.

17:06.607 --> 17:07.774
IT'S OKAY.

17:07.774 --> 17:10.343
HE WAS OLD,
BUT I LOVED HIM.

17:10.343 --> 17:12.278
SAD.
YEAH.

17:14.014 --> 17:15.949
ARE YOU OKAY?

17:15.949 --> 17:17.050
YEAH.

17:17.050 --> 17:19.052
I'M JUST
A LITTLE OVERWHELMED.

17:19.052 --> 17:21.187
WHY?
YOUR PARENTS.

17:21.187 --> 17:23.857
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT ABOUT THEM?

17:23.857 --> 17:27.493
ARE YOU SURE
THEY DON'T MIND ME BEING HERE?

17:27.493 --> 17:29.730
NO.
THEY DON'T MIND AT ALL.

17:32.599 --> 17:33.967
ARE YOU SURE?

17:33.967 --> 17:35.736
[ Chuckling ] YES.

17:35.736 --> 17:36.970
JUST RELAX.

17:36.970 --> 17:40.707
BUT IT'S YOUR FATHER'S
PRIVATE DINNER.

17:40.707 --> 17:41.975
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

17:41.975 --> 17:44.444
MY DAD LOVES WHEN GUESTS ARE
HERE AT THE HOUSE.

17:44.444 --> 17:45.879
ARE YOU SURE?

17:45.879 --> 17:50.416
YOU'VE ALREADY SAID THAT.
IT'S FINE.

17:50.416 --> 17:52.485
SO,
WHAT ARE YOU WEARING?

17:52.485 --> 17:55.789
I'M WEARING...

17:55.789 --> 17:57.423
THIS.

17:57.423 --> 17:58.925
WOW.

17:58.925 --> 18:01.167
THAT IS SO BEAUTIFUL.

18:01.167 --> 18:02.435
THANK YOU.

18:02.435 --> 18:03.469
WHAT ARE YOU WEARING?

18:03.469 --> 18:04.938
OH.

18:04.938 --> 18:06.472
LET'S SEE.

18:06.472 --> 18:07.941
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

18:11.244 --> 18:16.216
I MEAN
ONE OF THESE THREE.

18:16.216 --> 18:17.784
WOW.

18:17.784 --> 18:19.720
YEAH, MY MOM
JUST HAD THEM SENT OVER

18:19.720 --> 18:20.787
SO I COULD PICK ONE.

18:20.787 --> 18:22.155
WELL.

18:22.155 --> 18:24.224
SO,
WHICH ONE DO YOU THINK?

18:26.426 --> 18:28.962
I THINK
THEY ARE ALL REALLY NICE.

18:28.962 --> 18:29.996
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:29.996 --> 18:31.532
YOU DON'T LIKE THEM.

18:31.532 --> 18:33.199
NO, I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

18:33.199 --> 18:34.935
THEN WHAT IS IT?

18:37.538 --> 18:39.339
[ SIGHS ]
THEY'RE JUST SO...

18:39.339 --> 18:40.941
"SO" WHAT?

18:40.941 --> 18:43.744
MATRONLY.

18:43.744 --> 18:48.649
THEY DON'T SHOW
YOUR CURVES AND YOUR SKIN.

18:48.649 --> 18:50.383
I DON'T HAVE CURVES.

18:50.383 --> 18:53.987
YES, YOU DO.

18:53.987 --> 18:55.221
YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL.

18:55.221 --> 18:56.723
NO, I'M NOT.

18:56.723 --> 18:58.725
WHAT MIRROR ARE
YOU LOOKING INTO?

18:58.725 --> 19:01.234
[ Chuckling ]
COME ON, CANDACE.

19:01.234 --> 19:03.169
I'M NOT LIKE YOU.

19:03.169 --> 19:05.371
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

19:05.371 --> 19:08.341
I MEAN,
IF I HAD ALL THAT YOU HAVE...

19:08.341 --> 19:10.176
[CHUCKLES]
I WOULD BE HAPPY.

19:10.176 --> 19:13.213
I AM HAPPY.

19:13.213 --> 19:15.315
GOOD.

19:15.315 --> 19:16.817
COME ON,
LET'S TRY ON THESE DRESSES.

19:16.817 --> 19:18.384
NO.

19:18.384 --> 19:19.753
WHY?

19:19.753 --> 19:23.056
I'LL JUST TRY THEM ON
IN THE BATHROOM.

19:23.056 --> 19:24.725
WHY?

19:24.725 --> 19:28.428
I JUST LIKE TO TRY THEM ON
IN PRIVATE.

19:28.428 --> 19:30.396
[ CHUCKLES ] OKAY.
YOU DON'T MIND?

19:30.396 --> 19:32.198
NO. GO AHEAD.

19:32.198 --> 19:33.399
OKAY.
YEAH.

19:33.399 --> 19:35.502
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:47.714 --> 19:49.916
[ PIANO PLAYS SOFT JAZZ ]

19:58.825 --> 20:00.527
HAPPY BIRTHDAY,
OLD MAN.

20:00.527 --> 20:02.836
OH, SWEETHEART,
I'M OLDER THAN HE IS.

20:02.836 --> 20:04.204
WELL,
MAYBE HE'S IN BETTER SHAPE.

20:04.204 --> 20:06.039
OH.
[ LAUGHTER ]

20:06.039 --> 20:07.808
OH, HONEY.

20:09.175 --> 20:11.211
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.
THANK YOU.

20:11.211 --> 20:13.680
THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR THE GIFT.

20:13.680 --> 20:16.783
WELL, OPEN IT.

20:16.783 --> 20:18.351
OKAY.

20:20.386 --> 20:24.424
I'M GUESSING
MAYBE A TIE.

20:24.424 --> 20:25.726
NOW,
THAT'S NOT JUST ANY TIE.

20:25.726 --> 20:27.861
WE GOT IT
AT A CHARITY AUCTION.

20:27.861 --> 20:30.030
IT WAS ONCE WORN
BY A PRESIDENT.

20:30.030 --> 20:32.065
OR AT LEAST
THAT'S THE LIE THEY TOLD US

20:32.065 --> 20:33.667
TO GET US
TO PAY MORE FOR IT.

20:33.667 --> 20:35.068
[ LAUGHTER ]

20:35.068 --> 20:37.037
WHICH PRESIDENT?

20:37.037 --> 20:40.273
WE WON'T SAY,
OR YOUR FATHER WON'T WEAR IT.

20:40.273 --> 20:42.208
[ LAUGHTER ]
SMART WOMAN.

20:42.208 --> 20:44.645
YOU'LL WEAR IT.
IT WAS EXPENSIVE.

20:44.645 --> 20:45.679
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:45.679 --> 20:47.047
IT WAS FOR CHARITY.

20:47.047 --> 20:48.214
DAVID, STOP IT.

20:48.214 --> 20:49.550
WELL, THANK YOU.

20:49.550 --> 20:52.786
DAD, YOU'RE NOT USUALLY
THIS QUIET AROUND PEOPLE,

20:52.786 --> 20:54.855
ESPECIALLY
ON YOUR BIRTHDAY.

20:54.855 --> 20:56.256
WELL, IT'S BEEN

20:56.256 --> 21:00.827
A VERY [CHUCKLES] VERY LONG
AND TEDIOUS DAY, SWEETHEART,

21:00.827 --> 21:02.202
AND I CERTAINLY COULD USE
SOME BRANDY.

21:02.202 --> 21:03.570
OF COURSE.

21:03.570 --> 21:06.239
HANNA, WILL YOU BRING MR. CRYER
SOME BRANDY, PLEASE?

21:06.239 --> 21:09.810
AND WE NEED SOME MORE WINE
AND CHAMPAGNE AND ‐‐

21:09.810 --> 21:12.245
AND I'LL HAVE ONE, TOO, PLEASE.
BRANDY.

21:12.245 --> 21:13.379
UH, NO, HE WON'T.

21:13.379 --> 21:14.848
A SPARKLING WATER.

21:14.848 --> 21:16.049
TWO, PLEASE.

21:16.049 --> 21:19.052
AND SOME SPARKLING WATER
FOR THE HARRINGTONS, PLEASE.

21:21.121 --> 21:23.857
HANNA? DRINKS.

21:32.298 --> 21:35.201
SO, CANDACE,
YOU GO TO SCHOOL WITH AMANDA.

21:35.201 --> 21:36.603
YES, SHE DOES.

21:36.603 --> 21:37.871
YOU WOULD NOT BELIEVE
HOW BRILLIANT SHE IS.

21:37.871 --> 21:39.239
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:39.239 --> 21:40.774
ALL THE PROFESSORS
LOVE HER.

21:40.774 --> 21:42.776
[ SCOFFS ]
I BET THEY DO.

21:44.277 --> 21:46.947
SHE'S HELPING ME PREPARE
FOR AN EXAM NEXT WEEK.

21:46.947 --> 21:48.949
SO,
HOW IS LAW SCHOOL?

21:48.949 --> 21:50.584
DIFFICULT.

21:50.584 --> 21:52.619
DON'T WORRY.
I'LL SHOW HER HOW TO PASS.

21:52.619 --> 21:53.620
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:53.620 --> 21:55.088
THANK YOU.
YOU'RE WELCOME.

21:56.657 --> 22:00.026
I LOVE IT ‐‐
A SMART, STRONG YOUNG WOMAN.

22:00.026 --> 22:02.869
[ CHUCKLES ]
WE SHOULD TOAST <i>YOU.</i>

22:02.869 --> 22:04.470
THANK YOU.

22:04.470 --> 22:07.908
SO, CANDACE,
TELL US ABOUT YOUR FAMILY.

22:08.942 --> 22:13.947
MY DAD IS A DOCTOR
AT THE WINSLOW CANCER INSTITUTE.

22:13.947 --> 22:16.182
SO, SMART GENES RUN
IN YOUR FAMILY.

22:16.182 --> 22:17.751
MM‐HMM.

22:17.751 --> 22:19.452
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

22:19.452 --> 22:21.722
I HAVE A FRIEND
ON THE BOARD THERE.

22:21.722 --> 22:22.989
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:22.989 --> 22:25.358
HE'S A VERY PRIVATE PERSON,

22:25.358 --> 22:28.361
SO IF I MENTIONED HIM,
HE'D BE REALLY UPSET.

22:28.361 --> 22:29.696
OH, COME ON.

22:29.696 --> 22:33.066
NOW, SWEETHEART,
DON'T PRY.

22:33.066 --> 22:34.635
SHE FASCINATES ME.

22:34.635 --> 22:36.503
I LOVE
A SMART GIRL...

22:36.503 --> 22:37.538
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:37.538 --> 22:38.905
...IN LAW SCHOOL.

22:38.905 --> 22:40.240
YOU REMIND ME
OF MYSELF.

22:40.240 --> 22:42.643
Amanda: WELL,
SHE WAS BORN TO BE A LAWYER.

22:42.643 --> 22:44.010
I BET SHE IS.

22:44.010 --> 22:46.580
WORKING THE LAW.

22:47.981 --> 22:49.916
WYATT.
WHAT?

22:49.916 --> 22:51.117
STOP IT.

22:52.385 --> 22:53.386
YES, STOP IT.

22:53.386 --> 22:55.355
IT'S YOUR FATHER'S
BIRTHDAY.

22:55.355 --> 22:57.323
CAN'T YOU BEHAVE
JUST ONCE?

22:57.323 --> 22:58.525
MOM.

22:58.525 --> 22:59.760
I KNOW YOU ARE UPSET.

22:59.760 --> 23:00.861
UPSET?

23:00.861 --> 23:02.836
[ SCOFFS ]
YOU HAD ME COMMITTED.

23:04.571 --> 23:06.873
WE DID WHAT WE THOUGHT
WAS BEST FOR YOU.

23:06.873 --> 23:09.275
BY LOCKING ME AWAY
FOR MONTHS?

23:09.275 --> 23:11.545
WYATT, THEY WERE ONLY DOING
WHAT WAS BEST FOR YOU.

23:11.545 --> 23:13.279
OUR FACILITY HAS HAD
GREAT SUCCESS

23:13.279 --> 23:14.515
WITH THIS PARTICULAR
PROGRAM,

23:14.515 --> 23:17.083
AND OUR SON IS DOING
A WONDERFUL JOB.

23:17.083 --> 23:19.119
YES, AND YOU OUGHT TO BE
GRATEFUL

23:19.119 --> 23:21.121
INSTEAD OF SITTING THERE,
WHINING ALL DAY.

23:21.121 --> 23:22.222
GRATEFUL
THAT YOU LOCKED ME UP?

23:22.222 --> 23:23.824
YES.
YOU HAD A DRUG PROBLEM.

23:23.824 --> 23:24.858
WHAT WERE WE TO DO?

23:24.858 --> 23:25.959
RIGHT.

23:25.959 --> 23:28.762
YOU JUST DIDN'T WANT
ANYTHING TO RUIN

23:28.762 --> 23:30.664
YOUR PERFECT, LYING IMAGE.

23:31.932 --> 23:34.868
OKAY, CALM DOWN, WYATT,
OKAY?

23:34.868 --> 23:36.870
SO, CANDACE...

23:38.471 --> 23:40.373
...TELL US
ABOUT YOUR MOTHER.

23:44.811 --> 23:48.048
[ SIGHS ]

23:48.048 --> 23:52.185
MY MOM DIED
WHEN I WAS YOUNG.

23:52.185 --> 23:55.088
OH,
I'M SO SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

23:55.088 --> 23:56.923
YEAH.

24:03.303 --> 24:06.740
DARLING,
YOU'RE JUST STANDING THERE.

24:06.740 --> 24:07.941
SERVE THE DRINKS,
PLEASE.

24:14.748 --> 24:16.482
[ GASPS ]
Katheryn: HANNA!

24:16.482 --> 24:17.483
[ CLATTER ]

24:17.483 --> 24:19.452
I'M ‐‐ I'M SORRY.

24:20.754 --> 24:23.089
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

24:23.089 --> 24:24.390
LOOKS LIKE SILK TO ME.

24:25.659 --> 24:27.127
IS IT COLD IN HERE?

24:28.595 --> 24:30.130
[ SIGHS ]

24:30.130 --> 24:31.998
Katheryn:
I AM SO SORRY.

24:31.998 --> 24:33.600
SHE'S NEW.

24:33.600 --> 24:36.102
HANNA, KITCHEN,
PLEASE.

24:40.974 --> 24:43.677
SUCH A LOVELY DRESS.

24:43.677 --> 24:46.279
I'M GONNA GO AND CLEAN UP.

24:46.279 --> 24:47.714
I'LL SHOW YOU
WHERE IT IS.

24:47.714 --> 24:49.583
NO.

24:49.583 --> 24:53.253
I KNOW WHERE IT IS.
THANK YOU.

25:12.713 --> 25:15.348
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT SHE WAS THINKING.

25:15.348 --> 25:18.418
I HAVE NEVER HAD
ANYTHING LIKE THIS HAPPEN

25:18.418 --> 25:19.720
AT A PARTY.

25:19.720 --> 25:22.556
I KNOW
I SHOULD HAVE ‐‐

25:22.556 --> 25:25.526
THANK GOODNESS
THAT WASN'T THE GOVERNOR.

25:25.526 --> 25:27.160
HE WOULD NOT HAVE BEEN
SO FORGIVING.

25:27.160 --> 25:28.494
I AM SO SORRY.

25:28.494 --> 25:30.664
CELINE, WILL YOU DO THE SERVING,
PLEASE?

25:30.664 --> 25:32.398
YES, MA'AM.
OF COURSE.

25:32.398 --> 25:34.568
JUST STAY HERE.

25:34.568 --> 25:37.470
IF YOU WERE NERVOUS,
YOU SHOULD HAVE SAID SOMETHING.

25:37.470 --> 25:39.039
I'M SORRY.

26:00.561 --> 26:02.536
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

26:02.536 --> 26:04.705
WHAT ARE YOU UP TO?

26:04.705 --> 26:07.207
I'M NOT UP TO ANYTHING.

26:07.207 --> 26:08.975
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH THESE PEOPLE?

26:08.975 --> 26:11.578
AMANDA IS
A FRIEND OF MINE.

26:11.578 --> 26:13.213
YOU UP TO SOMETHING.

26:14.648 --> 26:15.782
I'M IN SCHOOL NOW.

26:15.782 --> 26:17.450
[ SCOFFS ] SCHOOL?

26:17.450 --> 26:19.586
YEAH. LAW SCHOOL.

26:19.586 --> 26:22.322
WHAT KIND OF CON OR GAME
ARE YOU RUNNING NOW?

26:22.322 --> 26:25.592
I'M NOT RUNNING
ANY GAME.

26:25.592 --> 26:27.928
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE I WENT WRONG WITH YOU.

26:27.928 --> 26:29.730
MM.

26:29.730 --> 26:32.098
I PRAY TO GOD EVERY DAY
THAT YOU'LL DO THE RIGHT THING.

26:32.098 --> 26:34.400
LOOK AT YOU.
DON'T.

26:34.400 --> 26:37.270
AND YOU'RE WITH
THAT LOWLIFE.

26:37.270 --> 26:39.540
WHAT'S HE GOT YOU DOING NOW,
HUH?

26:39.540 --> 26:41.675
YOU TRYING
TO ROB THESE PEOPLE?

26:41.675 --> 26:45.345
THIS IS
WHY I DO NOT TALK TO YOU.

26:45.345 --> 26:47.213
WHERE'S YOUR SON?

26:49.215 --> 26:50.617
YOU DON'T WORRY
ABOUT HIM.

26:51.718 --> 26:52.953
DO YOU HEAR ME?

26:52.953 --> 26:55.188
HE'S FINE.

26:55.188 --> 27:00.026
GIRL, SOMETHING BAD
IS GONNA HAPPEN TO YOU.

27:00.026 --> 27:01.267
YOU CAN'T KEEP
LIVING LIKE THIS.

27:01.267 --> 27:02.536
AND YOU CAN'T KEEP LIVING

27:02.536 --> 27:04.304
WITH YOUR HEAD BURIED
IN A BIBLE,

27:04.304 --> 27:06.106
TRYING TO HIDE
WHO YOU REALLY ARE.

27:06.106 --> 27:08.609
YOU KNOW, THE APPLE DOES NOT
FALL FAR FROM THE TREE.

27:08.609 --> 27:10.243
OH, GIRL,
YOU JUST LIKE YOUR FATHER.

27:10.243 --> 27:11.344
NO.

27:11.344 --> 27:13.079
MNH‐MNH.

27:13.079 --> 27:16.282
I'M MORE LIKE YOU
THAN YOU WILL ADMIT.

27:16.282 --> 27:21.354
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
I HAVE PEOPLE WAITING FOR ME.

27:21.354 --> 27:25.759
GO ON BACK TO YOUR MAIDING
AND FETCHING, MAMA.

27:25.759 --> 27:28.094
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:42.142 --> 27:44.344
HANNA.

27:44.344 --> 27:46.212
WHAT ‐‐ WHAT ‐‐
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

27:46.212 --> 27:48.515
YOU JUST GOT THIS JOB.
YOU KNOW BETTER THAN THAT.

27:48.515 --> 27:50.584
THAT'S MY DAUGHTER.
WHO?

27:50.584 --> 27:53.153
CANDACE ‐‐
THE GIRL IN THERE.

27:53.153 --> 27:54.621
WHAT?

27:54.621 --> 27:57.190
AND SHE'S UP TO SOMETHING.

27:57.190 --> 27:58.291
I KNOW HER.

27:58.291 --> 27:59.726
WAIT,
I‐I'VE KNOWN YOU FOR FOUR YEARS.

27:59.726 --> 28:01.334
YOU'VE NEVER TALKED TO ME
ABOUT A DAUGHTER.

28:01.334 --> 28:02.769
I PUT HER OUT OF MY HOUSE.

28:02.769 --> 28:05.238
SHE WAS HANGING
WITH THE WRONG CROWD.

28:05.238 --> 28:08.775
JUST BAD NEWS,
JUST TROUBLE.

28:08.775 --> 28:10.410
NOW I GOT TO GO IN THERE
AND TELL THESE PEOPLE ‐‐

28:10.410 --> 28:11.912
NO. NO.

28:11.912 --> 28:13.514
HANNA, DON'T.

28:13.514 --> 28:14.515
WHY NOT?

28:14.515 --> 28:16.082
BECAUSE I KNOW
THESE CRYERS,

28:16.082 --> 28:17.117
AND THEY'LL THINK

28:17.117 --> 28:18.351
THAT YOU HAD
SOMETHING TO DO WITH THIS.

28:18.351 --> 28:19.352
OH.

28:19.352 --> 28:20.554
SHE'S ONLY HERE
FOR THE WEEKEND.

28:20.554 --> 28:21.755
JUST ‐‐
JUST GET HER OUT OF HERE.

28:21.755 --> 28:23.790
JUST KEEP
YOUR MOUTH SHUT.

28:23.790 --> 28:24.858
WELL,
WHAT IF THEY FIND OUT?

28:24.858 --> 28:25.859
SHE DOESN'T WANT THEM TO,

28:25.859 --> 28:27.594
TRUST ME,
JUST LIKE YOU DON'T.

28:27.594 --> 28:30.096
I'VE WORKED HERE
FOR YEARS,

28:30.096 --> 28:32.465
AND YOU KNOW HOW I'VE MANAGED
TO KEEP THIS JOB?

28:32.465 --> 28:33.867
BY KEEPING MY MOUTH SHUT.

28:33.867 --> 28:36.402
YOU UNDERSTAND?
YEAH.

28:36.402 --> 28:37.771
OKAY, FINE.

28:37.771 --> 28:38.839
I'LL KEEP MY MOUTH SHUT

28:38.839 --> 28:40.273
UNTIL I CAN FIGURE OUT
WHAT TO DO.

28:40.273 --> 28:42.075
GOOD.
BUT I'M GONNA TELL YOU,

28:42.075 --> 28:44.578
THIS IS NOT GONNA END GOOD
AT ALL.

28:44.578 --> 28:45.779
I KNOW MY CHILD.

28:45.779 --> 28:48.281
MAYBE SHE'S CHANGED.
[ SCOFFS ]

28:48.281 --> 28:50.951
NO. NOT HER.

28:53.153 --> 28:54.387
HANNA, LOOK.

28:54.387 --> 28:56.156
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY,
REALLY.

28:58.058 --> 29:00.226
SHE WANTS YOU TO GO HOME,

29:00.226 --> 29:02.068
OHH.
JUST ‐‐ JUST FOR TONIGHT.

29:02.068 --> 29:04.905
WE'LL TRY AGAIN TOMORROW,
OKAY?

29:07.574 --> 29:10.176
THIS IS GONNA BE BAD,
CELINE.

29:12.813 --> 29:14.447
IT'S GONNA BE BAD.

29:17.818 --> 29:20.186
[ SIGHS ]

29:31.765 --> 29:33.734
YOU GOT IT.

29:33.734 --> 29:35.068
MM‐HMM.

29:35.068 --> 29:37.170
WHOO!
PRAISE THE LORD!

29:37.170 --> 29:38.404
IT'S NICE, RIGHT?

29:38.404 --> 29:39.706
I LIKE IT.

29:39.706 --> 29:41.174
FIRST TOW TRUCK.

29:41.174 --> 29:42.743
I TOLD YOU.

29:42.743 --> 29:44.210
SOON,
I'M GONNA HAVE A FLEET OF THEM.

29:44.210 --> 29:45.579
YES, YOU WILL, BABY.

29:45.579 --> 29:48.849
LOOK, MA, I KNOW THINGS ARE
KIND OF TIGHT AROUND HERE.

29:48.849 --> 29:51.484
I, UH...
I CALLED HIM UP.

29:51.484 --> 29:54.688
SAID I GOT
24 HOURS TO RETURN IT

29:54.688 --> 29:56.590
IF WE NEED ME
TO TAKE IT BACK, SO...

29:56.590 --> 29:58.291
OH, NO, SIR.

29:58.291 --> 30:00.627
THIS IS YOUR DREAM.
DON'T YOU DARE.

30:00.627 --> 30:02.435
DON'T YOU DARE.
[ LAUGHS ]

30:02.435 --> 30:05.205
HOW WAS YOUR FIRST DAY
WITH THE NEW FAMILY?

30:05.205 --> 30:07.674
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:07.674 --> 30:11.578
IT WAS FINE.
YEAH?

30:11.578 --> 30:13.547
UNTIL YOUR SISTER
SHOWED UP.

30:13.547 --> 30:15.081
SAY WHAT?

30:15.081 --> 30:17.217
YOUR SISTER SHOWED UP
AT THESE PEOPLE'S HOUSE

30:17.217 --> 30:18.351
WITH THEIR DAUGHTER,

30:18.351 --> 30:19.485
TALKING ABOUT
SHE WAS A COLLEGE STUDENT,

30:19.485 --> 30:20.821
LYING TO THESE PEOPLE.

30:20.821 --> 30:22.589
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

30:22.589 --> 30:24.490
I'M TELLING YOU
WHAT HAPPENED.

30:24.490 --> 30:27.761
AND SHE HAD THE NERVE TO SAY
THAT HER DADDY WAS A DOCTOR.

30:27.761 --> 30:30.496
YOU KNOW
HOW BAD I NEED THIS JOB.

30:30.496 --> 30:32.866
YEAH.
SHE GONNA MAKE ME LOSE IT.

30:32.866 --> 30:34.835
NO, SHE WON'T.
YES, SHE IS.

30:36.236 --> 30:37.771
SHE HATES ME, BENNY.

30:37.771 --> 30:38.772
MAMA,
SHE DON'T HATE YOU.

30:38.772 --> 30:40.373
YES, SHE DOES.

30:40.373 --> 30:43.544
SHE TOLD THOSE PEOPLE
THAT I WAS DEAD.

30:43.544 --> 30:46.346
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOUR SISTER,
LYING LIKE THAT,

30:46.346 --> 30:48.882
LYING ABOUT GOING
TO COLLEGE?

30:48.882 --> 30:50.551
I MEAN,
SHE IS IN SCHOOL.

30:52.185 --> 30:53.319
YOU KNEW ABOUT THIS?

30:55.689 --> 30:57.123
I MEAN, COME ON, MOM,
CUT HER A BREAK.

30:57.123 --> 30:58.224
YOU KNOW,
SHE'S IN COLLEGE.

30:58.224 --> 30:59.526
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

30:59.526 --> 31:01.735
I WAS AFRAID
YOU'D BE UPSET.

31:01.735 --> 31:04.705
I WASN'T GONNA BE UPSET
ABOUT HER GOING TO COLLEGE.

31:04.705 --> 31:07.107
I WANT TO KNOW
HOW SHE'S PAYING FOR IT.

31:07.107 --> 31:08.408
IS THAT BOY PAYING FOR IT?

31:08.408 --> 31:09.976
I'M NOT SURE, YOU KNOW?
SHE DIDN'T TELL ME.

31:09.976 --> 31:12.312
YEAH, I BET HE IS.

31:12.312 --> 31:17.518
LOOK, MA,
WHOEVER'S PAYING FOR IT,

31:17.518 --> 31:19.419
JUST LET IT BE,
ALL RIGHT?

31:19.419 --> 31:21.421
SHE'LL GET A JOB.
ALL RIGHT?

31:21.421 --> 31:22.923
SHE'LL GET HER LIFE TOGETHER,
YOU KNOW?

31:22.923 --> 31:24.257
IT'S ALL GOOD.

31:24.257 --> 31:26.026
COME ON,
I MADE YOUR FAVORITE.

31:26.026 --> 31:27.828
YEAH,
DON'T GET YOUR HOPES UP.

31:27.828 --> 31:29.930
THAT GIRL HAS
DISAPPOINTED ME AT EVERY TURN.

31:31.397 --> 31:33.266
AND WHERE IS HER BABY?

31:33.266 --> 31:34.768
SHE SAID SHE HAS A NANNY.

31:34.768 --> 31:36.002
A NANNY?

31:36.002 --> 31:37.437
[ SCOFFS ]

31:37.437 --> 31:39.806
THAT GIRL LEFT OUT OF HERE
18 MONTHS AGO, BROKE,

31:39.806 --> 31:41.007
AND NOW SHE GOT A NANNY?

31:42.509 --> 31:46.446
[ SIGHS ]

31:46.446 --> 31:48.782
SHE GONNA ROB THEM PEOPLE BLIND,
BENNY.

31:50.851 --> 31:52.519
MM.

31:52.519 --> 31:54.087
SHE'S JUST NO GOOD.

31:54.087 --> 31:55.622
THAT'S YOUR DAUGHTER
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

31:55.622 --> 31:57.924
AND SHE'S ALSO
HER FATHER'S DAUGHTER.

31:57.924 --> 31:59.826
I DON'T UNDERSTAND

31:59.826 --> 32:03.604
HOW TWO KIDS RAISED
IN THE SAME HOUSE

32:03.604 --> 32:05.238
CAN BE SO DIFFERENT.

32:06.439 --> 32:08.775
DIFFERENT DADDIES.

32:08.775 --> 32:09.810
BUT RELAX.

32:09.810 --> 32:10.844
YOU KNOW
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO BE

32:10.844 --> 32:12.145
WORKING UP YOUR BLOOD PRESSURE,
RIGHT?

32:12.145 --> 32:13.547
MM‐HMM.
COME ON.

32:13.547 --> 32:14.615
I MADE YOU SOME DINNER.

32:14.615 --> 32:17.350
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'D DO WITHOUT YOU.

32:17.350 --> 32:19.620
STARVE.
THAT'S WHAT YOU'D DO.

32:19.620 --> 32:21.855
David:
GOOD NIGHT, SON.

32:21.855 --> 32:23.957
WELL, HAPPY BIRTHDAY.
IT'S OVER NOW.

32:23.957 --> 32:25.258
HEY, ENJOY YOURSELF.

32:25.258 --> 32:26.459
IT GETS BETTER NOW
AFTER 50.

32:26.459 --> 32:28.094
THAT'S WHAT I'VE HEARD.
I'LL GET YOUR CAR.

32:28.094 --> 32:30.931
WE NEED TO TALK.
Jim: MM‐HMM.

32:30.931 --> 32:32.833
THAT WAS LOVELY.

32:32.833 --> 32:34.167
THANK YOU.

32:34.167 --> 32:36.703
AND THANK YOU
FOR THE WONDERFUL GIFT.

32:36.703 --> 32:38.238
[ CHUCKLES ]
SEE YOU LATER.

32:38.238 --> 32:40.073
ABSOLUTELY.
BYE.

32:40.073 --> 32:43.944
OH, KATHERYN.

32:43.944 --> 32:46.246
I'M NOT SO SURE
ABOUT THAT GIRL.

32:46.246 --> 32:47.480
WHO?

32:51.885 --> 32:53.987
[ SCOFFS ]
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

32:53.987 --> 32:57.190
NOT WANTING TO TELL US
HER FATHER'S NAME?

32:57.190 --> 33:00.193
MAYBE SHE HAS
GOOD REASON.

33:00.193 --> 33:03.403
OR MAYBE SHE'S LYING.

33:03.403 --> 33:04.538
WATCH HER.

33:04.538 --> 33:08.008
OKAY.

33:08.008 --> 33:09.375
GOOD NIGHT.

33:09.375 --> 33:11.845
GOOD NIGHT.

33:11.845 --> 33:12.946
GOOD NIGHT, JIM.

33:12.946 --> 33:15.181
GOOD NIGHT.
THANKS AGAIN FOR THE TIE.

33:15.181 --> 33:16.650
GOOD NIGHT,
KATHERYN.

33:16.650 --> 33:17.718
GOOD NIGHT.

33:17.718 --> 33:20.486
DAD, AREN'T YOU GONNA
STAY UP AND TALK?

33:20.486 --> 33:22.723
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
IN FOREVER.

33:22.723 --> 33:24.658
SWEETHEART, I'VE ‐‐
I'VE HAD A VERY TRYING DAY.

33:24.658 --> 33:26.192
I'M JUST GONNA GET SOME REST,
OKAY?

33:26.192 --> 33:27.393
OKAY. I LOVE YOU.

33:27.393 --> 33:29.229
I LOVE YOU, TOO,
SWEETIE.

33:32.699 --> 33:34.234
GOOD NIGHT, MOM.

33:34.234 --> 33:35.401
Katheryn:
GOOD NIGHT, SWEETIE.

33:37.103 --> 33:38.872
GOOD NIGHT.

33:44.044 --> 33:45.712
GOOD NIGHT.

33:45.712 --> 33:47.347
GOOD NIGHT.

34:18.318 --> 34:20.621
WELL,
THAT WAS LOVELY.

34:20.621 --> 34:22.455
YES, IT WAS.

34:22.455 --> 34:24.090
THANK YOU.

34:24.090 --> 34:25.592
WHAT'S GOING ON?

34:25.592 --> 34:26.927
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

34:26.927 --> 34:29.162
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:29.162 --> 34:31.732
I'VE BEEN MARRIED TO YOU
FOR 25 YEARS.

34:31.732 --> 34:34.000
I KNOW
WHEN SOMETHING'S GOING ON.

34:34.000 --> 34:35.435
WHAT IS IT?

34:35.435 --> 34:37.403
NOTHING.

34:37.403 --> 34:40.006
OKAY.

34:40.006 --> 34:41.107
WHAT'S HER NAME?

34:41.107 --> 34:42.909
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

34:42.909 --> 34:44.611
YOU CAUGHT ME.

34:44.611 --> 34:45.979
HER NAME IS AMANDA.

34:45.979 --> 34:47.714
PERHAPS YOU'VE MET HER.
SHE'S OUR DAUGHTER.

34:47.714 --> 34:48.715
SHE CUTS HERSELF.

34:48.715 --> 34:49.750
OR HIS NAME IS WYATT.

34:49.750 --> 34:51.217
MAYBE YOU'VE MET HIM,
TOO.

34:51.217 --> 34:52.452
HE'S OUR SON.
HE'S IN REHAB.

34:52.452 --> 34:54.220
ARE YOU SURE
THAT'S ALL IT IS?

34:54.220 --> 34:56.790
TODAY, I'M 50 YEARS OLD.

34:56.790 --> 34:59.125
MY DAUGHTER NEEDS THERAPY.
SHE REFUSES IT.

34:59.125 --> 35:03.436
MY SON IS IN THERAPY.
HE'S DOING VERY POORLY.

35:03.436 --> 35:05.305
AND THEN, OF COURSE,
THERE'S YOU AND I.

35:05.305 --> 35:06.540
WE'RE DOING SO WELL.

35:06.540 --> 35:08.374
YEAH. I'VE GOT THAT.

35:10.376 --> 35:12.579
BUT WE DO HAVE
A LOT TO BE THANKFUL FOR,

35:12.579 --> 35:14.648
AND THAT'S SOMETHING
WE SHOULD FOCUS ON

35:14.648 --> 35:16.349
AND HOPE
THAT THEY FIND THEIR WAY,

35:16.349 --> 35:19.085
SUCH AS IT IS.

35:19.085 --> 35:22.255
WHATEVER IT IS THAT WE HAVE
TO BE THANKFUL FOR,

35:22.255 --> 35:23.790
DO ME A FAVOR.

35:23.790 --> 35:27.861
PUT A YELLOW STICKY ON IT
SO I'LL RECOGNIZE IT.

35:27.861 --> 35:29.696
Amanda: [ SIGHS ]
I'M STARVING.

35:29.696 --> 35:30.997
Candace:
I AM, TOO.

35:30.997 --> 35:32.398
YEAH,
THAT ACTUALLY SOUNDS GREAT.

35:32.398 --> 35:33.399
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:33.399 --> 35:34.400
YOU WANT SOMETHING,
WYATT?

35:34.400 --> 35:37.070
UH, NO, THANKS.
I'M GOOD.

35:37.070 --> 35:39.205
MMM, MMM, MMM.

35:39.205 --> 35:41.041
Benny:
GOOD NIGHT, MAMA.

35:47.881 --> 35:50.416
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

35:50.416 --> 35:51.652
[ SIGHS ]

35:51.652 --> 35:53.854
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

35:53.854 --> 35:55.421
SOMEBODY'S PURSE IS
VIBRATING.

35:57.090 --> 35:59.893
OH, THAT'S MINE.

35:59.893 --> 36:02.068
THANKS.

36:02.068 --> 36:04.070
[ VIBRATING CONTINUES ]

36:08.274 --> 36:09.442
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

36:09.442 --> 36:10.443
HELLO?

36:10.443 --> 36:11.712
IS THAT YOUR BOYFRIEND?

36:11.712 --> 36:13.914
HOLD ON ONE SECOND.

36:13.914 --> 36:15.015
NO.

36:15.015 --> 36:17.183
IS THERE A PLACE
I COULD TAKE THIS?

36:17.183 --> 36:18.952
YOU CAN TAKE IT
IN MY DAD'S OFFICE.

36:18.952 --> 36:20.621
IT'S THE SECOND DOOR
ON THE LEFT.

36:20.621 --> 36:22.523
SECOND DOOR ON THE LEFT.
OKAY, THANKS.

36:22.523 --> 36:24.991
MM‐HMM.

36:43.443 --> 36:45.946
HELLO?

36:45.946 --> 36:48.481
CANDACE,
MOM IS VERY UPSET OVER HERE.

36:48.481 --> 36:49.616
WHAT'S GOING ON?

36:49.616 --> 36:51.685
I DIDN'T KNOW SHE WORKED HERE,
BENNY.

36:51.685 --> 36:53.019
WELL, THEN,
WHY DON'T YOU LEAVE?

36:53.019 --> 36:54.254
I CAN'T.

36:54.254 --> 36:56.189
Why?

36:56.189 --> 37:00.126
BECAUSE AMANDA IS MY FRIEND
AND I'M HELPING HER.

37:00.126 --> 37:02.368
Tell her to find
another job.

37:02.368 --> 37:04.037
NO, SHE NEEDS THAT ONE.

37:04.037 --> 37:06.773
[ SIGHS ] IS THIS
WHAT YOU CALLED ME ABOUT?

37:06.773 --> 37:08.341
THAT AND TO MAKE SURE

37:08.341 --> 37:09.609
YOU'RE PAYING THE MORTGAGE
THIS MONTH.

37:09.609 --> 37:13.212
YES.
I TOLD YOU I WOULD.

37:13.212 --> 37:15.081
IS THAT ALL?

37:15.081 --> 37:17.316
Candace, Mama thinks
you're up to something.

37:19.586 --> 37:20.587
[ SCOFFS ]

37:20.587 --> 37:21.622
PLEASE TELL ME

37:21.622 --> 37:22.956
YOU'RE NOT UP
TO YOUR OLD TRICKS, "C."

37:22.956 --> 37:25.692
NO. I'VE CHANGED.

37:25.692 --> 37:27.127
WHY CAN'T SHE
BELIEVE THAT?

37:27.127 --> 37:28.895
BECAUSE IT'S MAMA.

37:28.895 --> 37:30.063
[ SIGHS ]

37:30.063 --> 37:32.032
LOOK, I GOT TO GO.

37:32.032 --> 37:33.366
Wait. Wait.

37:35.268 --> 37:36.402
I FINALLY GOT IT.

37:36.402 --> 37:38.905
[ Chuckling ]
OH, MY GOODNESS.

37:38.905 --> 37:40.841
BENNY,
YOU GOT THE TOW TRUCK?

37:40.841 --> 37:43.510
YEAH. [ CHUCKLES ]

37:43.510 --> 37:45.879
YEAH, I BOUGHT IT TODAY ‐‐
CASH.

37:48.348 --> 37:51.284
I AM SO HAPPY FOR YOU.

37:51.284 --> 37:53.086
YOU'VE WANTED TO BE
A TOW‐TRUCK DRIVER

37:53.086 --> 37:54.487
SINCE YOU WERE
A LITTLE KID.

37:54.487 --> 37:57.558
MAN,
I AM SO PROUD OF YOU.

37:57.558 --> 38:00.594
IT LOOKS LIKE WE'RE BOTH
ON THE CUSP OF OUR DREAMS.

38:00.594 --> 38:01.735
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

38:01.735 --> 38:02.936
I'LL CALL YOU LATER.

38:02.936 --> 38:04.037
ALL RIGHT.

38:04.037 --> 38:05.205
I LOVE YOU.

38:05.205 --> 38:07.708
I LOVE YOU MORE.

38:07.708 --> 38:09.710
[ LAUGHS ] BYE.

38:09.710 --> 38:11.077
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
OKAY.

38:27.060 --> 38:29.596
[ DOOR CREAKS OPEN ]

38:34.701 --> 38:36.503
[ MUFFLED SHOUT ]
Shh, Shh, Shh.

39:13.614 --> 39:15.215
HOW THE HELL LONG
HAVE YOU KNOWN MY DAUGHTER?

39:15.215 --> 39:17.050
THIS SEMESTER.

39:17.050 --> 39:19.953
DOES SHE KNOW WHAT YOU DO?
NO.

39:19.953 --> 39:20.954
[ SIGHS ]

39:20.954 --> 39:23.056
I'M SORRY
THAT THIS HAPPENED.

39:23.056 --> 39:24.825
I HAD NO IDEA.

39:24.825 --> 39:27.260
I ‐‐ I HOPE I DIDN'T RUIN
YOUR BIRTHDAY.

39:27.260 --> 39:29.796
YEAH.
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN.

39:29.796 --> 39:31.431
TOMORROW MORNING,
WE'RE ALL GONNA GET TOGETHER

39:31.431 --> 39:32.633
FOR BREAKFAST AT 7:00,

39:32.633 --> 39:34.434
AND THEN I WANT YOU
TO COME UP WITH SOME EXCUSE

39:34.434 --> 39:35.636
AS TO WHY
YOU HAVE TO LEAVE,

39:35.636 --> 39:37.070
AND YOU'RE GONNA
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE,

39:37.070 --> 39:38.839
AND YOU'RE NEVER GONNA
SPEAK TO MY DAUGHTER AGAIN.

39:38.839 --> 39:39.906
JIM ‐‐

39:39.906 --> 39:41.341
DID I MAKE MYSELF CLEAR?

39:43.777 --> 39:45.912
I WILL NOT CAUSE YOU
ANY HARM.

39:45.912 --> 39:48.782
NO,
BECAUSE YOU WON'T BE HERE.

39:48.782 --> 39:51.552
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:51.552 --> 39:57.123
SO, WHAT YOU SAID ABOUT
WANTING TO SEE ME AGAIN...

39:57.123 --> 39:59.159
YOU DIDN'T MEAN IT?

39:59.159 --> 40:00.934
REALLY?

40:00.934 --> 40:02.869
NO, OF COURSE NOT.
NOT LIKE THIS.

40:02.869 --> 40:07.073
SO, I'M ONLY GOOD ENOUGH
FOR THE DARK.

40:07.073 --> 40:11.044
YOU DON'T KNOW ME.
I DON'T KNOW YOU.

40:11.044 --> 40:12.846
OKAY, YOU'RE IN MY HOUSE.
YOU'RE AMONG MY FAMILY.

40:12.846 --> 40:15.381
YOU DON'T BELONG HERE.
GET A GRIP.

40:15.381 --> 40:17.751
I WANT YOU
TO GET UP IN THE MORNING

40:17.751 --> 40:19.219
AND GET
OUT OF MY HOUSE SOON.

40:19.219 --> 40:20.220
JUST DO IT.

40:20.220 --> 40:22.689
I DON'T THINK SO.

40:25.291 --> 40:26.560
I'M SORRY.
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

40:28.394 --> 40:29.796
YOU HAVE A HEARING PROBLEM,
HUH?

40:29.796 --> 40:31.865
NO, I HEAR PRETTY GOOD.
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

40:31.865 --> 40:34.935
"I DON'T THINK SO."

40:34.935 --> 40:38.304
I WANT $100,000,

40:38.304 --> 40:41.174
AND I LOVE THAT LITTLE CAR

40:41.174 --> 40:43.476
YOU BOUGHT
FOR YOUR DAUGHTER, AMANDA.

40:43.476 --> 40:44.778
DO YOU?
MM‐HMM.

40:44.778 --> 40:47.013
WELL, LISTEN TO ME,
LITTLE GIRL.

40:47.013 --> 40:48.882
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHO YOU'RE DEALING WITH.

40:51.585 --> 40:56.990
LIKE I SAID...
$100,000 CASH...

40:59.526 --> 41:02.168
...OR...

41:02.168 --> 41:04.905
I BURN
YOUR LITTLE PLAYHOUSE DOWN.

41:36.970 --> 41:38.839
<i>NEXT WEEK ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:38.839 --> 41:40.073
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

41:40.073 --> 41:41.842
I THINK YOU AND JEFFREY
COULD MAKE A NICE COUPLE.

41:41.842 --> 41:43.944
WHO'S JEFFREY?
UH.

41:43.944 --> 41:46.513
IS JEFFREY GAY?
WHAT?

41:46.513 --> 41:48.749
HAVE YOU EVER WANTED
TO LIVE LIKE THIS, MAMA?

41:48.749 --> 41:50.150
I'M NOT PLAYING
WITH YOU.

41:50.150 --> 41:52.886
I'M JUST GLAD I WAS ABLE
TO PUT THE HOUSE IN YOUR NAME.

41:52.886 --> 41:54.154
IF IT GETS TOO BAD,

41:54.154 --> 41:55.388
THEY WON'T BE ABLE
TO TAKE IT FROM US.

41:55.388 --> 41:56.990
SO,
WHO DO THEY WANT TO RUN?

41:56.990 --> 41:58.859
THEY WANT YOU TO RUN.

41:58.859 --> 42:01.935
MAYBE WE COULD DO IT
AT THE HOUSE IN THE OFFICE.

42:03.036 --> 42:04.905
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
